      "message": "[warning] Line 128: Only the luma plane (data[0]) is initialized; VideoFrame::reserve() allocates via FFmpeg without zeroing, so the U/V planes (data[1]/data[2]) are read uninitialized by scale() and scale_and_pad(). This is harmless for the luma[0][0] assertion but will trip MemorySanitizer/Valgrind in CI. Initialize the chroma planes too, e.g. after the luma memset:\n```suggestion\n    memset(in-\u003edata[0], LUMA, static_cast\u003csize_t\u003e(in-\u003elinesize[0]) * in-\u003eheight);\n    memset(in-\u003edata[1], 0x80, static_cast\u003csize_t\u003e(in-\u003elinesize[1]) * ((in-\u003eheight + 1) / 2));\n    memset(in-\u003edata[2], 0x80, static_cast\u003csize_t\u003e(in-\u003elinesize[2]) * ((in-\u003eheight + 1) / 2));\n```",
